          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " in donations from PACs and employees in the industry.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A Side Deal Could Be Another Gift",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In exchange for his vote for the IRA, Manchin convinced Schumer and House Speaker Nancy Pelosi (D-Calif.) to agree to hold votes on a separate bill that would accelerate the permitting process for energy projects ‚Äî including potentially for a proposed Enterprise oil terminal that has long been delayed.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Since January 2019, the federal government has been sitting on an application from Enterprise to build a massive facility off the coast of Texas that would be the first U.S. terminal capable of accommodating the world‚Äôs largest supertankers ‚Äî known as very large crude containers, or VLCCs ‚Äî that can hold up to two million barrels of oil and are too large to enter shallow waters.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "callout",
        "calloutEmoji": "üí°",
        "calloutText": "Follow us on <a href=\"https://apple.news/TeRci1RtoQfWCNA5h7NTBlg\">Apple News</a> and <a href=\"https://news.google.com/publications/CAAqBwgKMPvKngswktW2Aw\">Google News</a> to make sure you see our stories first, and to help make sure others see our breaking news as well.",
        "backgroundColor": "grey"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The project, known as the Sea Port Oil Terminal (SPOT), is strongly opposed by environmentalists who have filed thousands of comments with the U.S. Maritime Administration, the agency overseeing the application. Critics of the terminal warn that the project could cause oil spills and exacerbate the climate crisis by accelerating oil extraction.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Enterprise Products has had to repeatedly extend its timeline for the project due to government inaction, most recently blowing past the ‚Äúmid-2022‚Äù estimate it gave shareholders in its annual report for last year. The text of Manchin‚Äôs bill has not yet been released, but according to the ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 2,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Washington Post",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.washingtonpost.com/us-policy/2022/08/01/manchin-pipeline-drilling-permit/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", it would set a two-year time limit for the government to review applications for ‚Äúmajor‚Äù energy projects, and it would make it harder for the government to deny projects because of environmental impacts that are not directly caused by the project itself.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
